com.anaplan.client

Class Program

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.anaplan.client.Program
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MockProgram

    public abstract class Program
extends java.lang.Object
    A command-line interface to the Anaplan Connect API library. Running the program with no arguments will display the available options. This class also contains several static convenience methods that may be useful by other alternative main-method implementations - these should extend this class to gain access to them as they have protected access.

      • promptForValue

        protected static java.lang.String promptForValue(java.lang.String propertyName,
                                                 java.lang.String propertyValue,
                                                 boolean password)
        Check and if necessary prompt for a value. If propertyValue is null, empty or '?', and the program is associated with a terminal (ie System.console() != null), then prompt the user using the value in propertyName, followed by a colon. If password is true, then the value input by the user will not be echoed.
        Parameters:
        propertyName - the value to be displayed to the user if prompted
        propertyValue - the value supplied
        password - flag to suppress echoing
        Returns:
        the value passed in propertyValue, or the value entered by the user if it was necessary to prompt
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if there is no terminal associated with the program and a value was not supplied.
        Since:
        1.3
